# Vulnerable code in trim is not used in Fleet

CVE-2020-7753

# We feel like the risk of DoS using this technique, which requires being logged in, is low probability and low impact, as such we will not update glob-parent only for this CVE

CVE-2020-28469

# 2024/04/04 (github.com/goreleaser/nfpm/v2 should be updated)
# When packaging linux files, we do not use global permissions. Manually verified that packed fleet-osquery files do not have group/global write permissions.

CVE-2023-32698

# 2026/06/18 — github.com/docker/docker is no longer used directly by Fleet; the
# upgrade-test client was migrated to github.com/moby/moby/client. docker/docker
# remains as an indirect transitive dep through go-sysinfo (via elastic apm),
# which only references `api/types` definitions. None of these CVEs affect the
# Docker daemon code paths, which Fleet does not compile or run. Moby v29+ (the
# fixed line) is published under a new module path (github.com/moby/moby/v2),
# so the indirect dep cannot be bumped without changes upstream in go-sysinfo.

CVE-2026-34040
CVE-2026-41567
CVE-2026-42306
CVE-2026-33997
CVE-2026-41568
